==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sheik
<hw>Sheik</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>sheikh</ets>, <ets>shaykh</ets>, a venerable old man, a chief, fr.
<ets>sh⟦amac⟧kha</ets> to grow or be old.]</ety> <def>The head of an
Arab family, or of a clan or a tribe; also, the chief magistrate of an
Arab village. The name is also applied to Mohammedan ecclesiastics of a
high grade.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>scheik</asp>,
<asp>shaik</asp>, <asp>sheikh</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

